The paper discusses prevention mechanisms for DDoS attacks on Internet services, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses network infrastructure and communication protocols, which are relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the strengths and weaknesses of different prevention mechanisms, which is relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of DDoS attacks on network performance, which is relevant to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the need for effective prevention mechanisms, which is relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
